<TITLE> UK drawn to Dhaka call centres at Expo 2008 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 16 (bdnews24.com)  UK companies have shown interest in setting up call centres in Bangladesh after a presentation by Dhaka regulatory officials at a Birmingham exposition, a BTRC official said Tuesday. BTRC chairman, Manzurul Alam, gave a presentation on the telecommunication industry, explaining why Bangladesh could be a good destination for call centres of big UK companies, said Abdullah Ferdous, a BTRC consultant. The two-day Call Centre Expo 2008 began in the British midlands city Tuesday. "Bangladesh is not just a country of natural disasters. We have resources. The telecommunication sector offers a huge potential," the BTRC chief was quoted to have told his audience. "We are capable of offering world class service. Foreign companies should come and invest." Telecommunications secretary Iqbal Mahmud and Board of Investment Chairman Kamal Uddin also travelled to Birmingham for the Call Centre Expo. Seven Bangladeshi firms joined the expo to explore opportunities: InGen Technology, Aamra Outsourcing Ltd, HMC Technology Ltd, Iqra Media Centre, Legato Services Ltd, Orbit Communications and Windmill Advertising Ltd. The BTRC started giving licence for call centre in April. The telecoms regulator issued 310 licences in three categories  Call Centre, Hosted Call Centre and Hosed Call Centre Service Provider. b
